               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of al-Qurʾān</summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/n79046204 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh85116261" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_144x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="ar" otherLangs="fa">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_112">al-Qurʾān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_112">القرآن</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Complete, but damaged and thoroughly disordered copy of the Arabic Qurʾān with occasional annotations and corrections in the margins.</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon: completed … for 
                <persName key="person_f8110" role="dte">Masīḥ al-Zamān Khān the ṭabīb</persName>… (date obscured). Datable to the late eighteenth century.
                        </p>
                        <p>Not foliated.</p>
                        <p>Indications in margins for sujūd, rukūʿāt, aḥzāb (s̲uls̲, rubʿ, khams, niṣf, and so on) in coloured inks.</p>
                        <p>Rough naskh; annotations in various cursive hands.</p>
                        <p>Crude illumination added (probably later) throughout.</p>
                        <p>Metallic pigments oxidised.</p>
                        <p>Lacking original covers.</p>
                        <p>Folios unbound and disordered; wormholes, stains, creases, smudging, tearing, unevenly cropped, later repairs.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
